    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen running `:syntax off` in Neovim 0.11.3 (macOS 15.5), syntax highlighting is disabled for most filetypes as expected, but it remains active for `help` files, `.lua` files, and `.query` files. Highlighting persists in these filetypes even after disabling syntax.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open a help file (`:help`), or any `.lua` or `.query` file.\n2. Execute `:syntax off`.\n3. Observe that syntax highlighting stays enabled for these files.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSyntax highlighting should be fully disabled across all filetypes after running `:syntax off`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
