            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "**suggestion:** Since syntax highlighting is on by default, it might be helpful to check `g:syntax_on` before starting Tree-sitter, like this:\n\n```lua\nif vim.fn.exists(\"g:syntax_on\") == 1 then\n  vim.treesitter.start()\nend\n```\n\n**note:** this still does not turn off syntax highlighting if we are already in a file and try `:syntax off` in `help` file or `lua` or `query` files.",
